-- Kuwait Finance House Unit Acquires 67% of Aref Energy
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2012-08-01T11:51:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/kuwait-finance-house-unit-acquires-67-of-aref-energy.html
Development Enterprises Holding, a
unit of  Kuwait Finance House (KFIN) , completed the acquisition of 66.8
percent of  Aref Energy Holding (AREFENRG)  KSCC, according to a statement to
the Kuwait Stock Exchange today.  Development Enterprises purchased 500.7 million shares at
134 fils per share, valuing the acquisition at 67.1 million
dinars ($238 million), the company said. Aref Energy is a unit
of Aref Investment Group.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
 fmacdonald4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew in Dubai at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  